Author: ComputerGenie#2331
Content: value for Z9 vs mini is "better" if, and only if, the assumption holds true that the z9 has 4x chips

Author: ComputerGenie#2331
Content: however, if the Z9 has less chips that are already OCed, then minis are greater in value

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: gamble that they hold more chips?

Author: ComputerGenie#2331
Content: The chance that the Z9 has more chips than 4x the mini and those chips are underclocked is an infinitesimal chance at best

Author: ComputerGenie#2331
Content:
from a manufacturing standpoint, the only 2 real options are:
Z9 has 4x chips
Z9 has less chips and those chips are running at a higher multiplier than that of the minis

Given those choices, it stands to reason that the manufacturer's better option for higher profit yields is the latter
